# GSAP for Inabiya Ecommerce (2026)

GSAP is primary for marketing/scroll/storytelling motion on Soft Gift storefront. Framer Motion only for tiny UI (toast/presence micro-interactions). Do not animate everything.

## Setup (required)

- Client leaf only: `'use client'`
- Use `@gsap/react` → `useGSAP()` for create + auto cleanup/context
- Register plugins client-side only:
  `if (typeof window !== 'undefined') gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger)`
- Never call `gsap.*` / `ScrollTrigger.*` during SSR/render
- Scope selectors to a container `ref` (no global `'.card'` across the app)

## Performance

- Prefer `transform` + `opacity` (compositor-friendly)
- Avoid animating layout props (`top/left/width/height`) unless Flip needs it
- Batch lists with `ScrollTrigger.batch` when many similar reveals
- `ScrollTrigger.refresh()` after fonts/images/layout shifts
- Kill/cleanup on route change (useGSAP handles if scoped correctly)
- Code-split heavy scenes with `next/dynamic` + `ssr: false` when bundle weight hurts LCP

## Accessibility

If `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`:

- Skip pin / scrub / parallax / big timelines
- Keep final content visible (no opacity 0 traps)
- Don’t rely on animation to reveal critical CTA/price/stock

## Ecommerce UX (Soft Gift)

Use GSAP for: hero presence, collection reveals, PDP gallery polish, Build-Your-Box step transitions, soft scroll storytelling on marketing pages.

Do NOT use heavy GSAP on: checkout pay path, cart line edits, admin tables, input typing — keep crisp & instant.

Match Design.md: calm premium motion (≈0.2–0.6s), not flashy SaaS bounce spam. 2–3 intentional motions per polished view beat 20 weak ones.

## Hydration safety

Server and client JSX trees must match. Don’t branch markup on `window`. Animate after mount via useGSAP only.

## Checklist before merging animation work

- [ ] useGSAP scoped · [ ] reduced-motion path · [ ] no SSR window crash · [ ] mobile pin sane or disabled · [ ] LCP image not delayed by animation · [ ] CTAs clickable during/after motion
